sequenceDiagram
    participant Host as Game Host
    participant API as Game Server API
    participant Judge as LLM Judge
    participant DB as Database
    
    Note over Host,DB: Ultra-Radical Rules-Based Card System Initialization
    
    Host->>API: POST /games/{gameId}/start
    activate API
    
    Note over API: Step 1: Load Initial Rules
    API->>DB: Load initial-rules-v1.0.0.json
    DB-->>API: Initial rules (including meta-rules)
    
    Note over API,Judge: Step 2: Compile Card System Meta-Rules
    API->>Judge: POST /compile-rules<br/>(INIT-001 to INIT-004)
    activate Judge
    
    Note over Judge: Parse meta-rules:<br/>- Card structure (suit, rank)<br/>- Available suits<br/>- Available ranks<br/>- Deck composition
    
    Judge->>Judge: Generate card definitions<br/>from meta-rules
    
    Judge-->>API: Compiled card system:<br/>{cardDefinitions: {...}}
    deactivate Judge
    
    Note over API: Step 3: Create Deck from Card Definitions
    API->>API: Generate 54 card instances<br/>based on compiled definitions
    
    API->>DB: Store cardDefinitions in game state
    DB-->>API: Stored
    
    Note over API,Judge: Step 4: Compile Gameplay Rules
    API->>Judge: POST /compile-rules<br/>(INIT-005 to INIT-009)
    activate Judge
    
    Note over Judge: Compile gameplay rules:<br/>- Card matching<br/>- Wild cards<br/>- Draw rules<br/>- Win conditions<br/>- Turn order
    
    Judge-->>API: Compiled gameplay rules
    deactivate Judge
    
    API->>DB: Store compiled rules
    DB-->>API: Stored
    
    Note over API: Step 5: Deal Initial Hands
    API->>API: Shuffle deck<br/>Deal 7 cards to each player
    
    API->>DB: Update game state:<br/>- status: in_progress<br/>- player hands<br/>- deck cardIds<br/>- discard pile
    DB-->>API: Updated
    
    API-->>Host: 200 OK<br/>Game started with<br/>rules-based card system
    deactivate API
    
    Note over Host,DB: Card system is now fully defined by rules,<br/>not hardcoded in schemas!